Evidence

Your NooBaa deployment is 523 days old:

NooBaa CR age: 523d
noobaa-admin secret age: 523d

But the PostgreSQL database was recreated only recently:

StatefulSet noobaa-db-pg creationTimestamp: 2026-06-18
PVC db-noobaa-db-pg-0 age: 6d

At the same time, NooBaa continuously reports:

account not found 6788bafb4b40bd002623d3a0

This means:

1. The original NooBaa database was lost/recreated around June 18.


2. The old noobaa-admin secret still contains credentials pointing to the old admin account.


3. The recreated database does not contain that account ID.


4. Authentication fails.


5. BackingStore remains Connecting.


6. BucketClass remains Verifying.


7. NooBaa remains Configuring.


8. StorageCluster remains Progressing.



