So there is no object storage metadata that needs protection.


---

Recommended Recovery

Before changing anything, save the current objects:

oc get noobaa noobaa -n openshift-storage -o yaml > /tmp/noobaa.yaml
oc get backingstore -n openshift-storage -o yaml > /tmp/backingstore.yaml
oc get bucketclass -n openshift-storage -o yaml > /tmp/bucketclass.yaml

Then check whether the operator recreates NooBaa automatically after deletion:

oc delete noobaa noobaa -n openshift-storage

Watch:

oc get noobaa -n openshift-storage -w

If it is not recreated automatically within a few minutes:

oc delete pod -l app=ocs-operator -n openshift-storage

oc annotate storagecluster ocs-storagecluster \
  -n openshift-storage \
  reconcile-now="$(date +%s)" --overwrite


---

Alternative (less disruptive)

Before deleting the NooBaa CR, you can try restarting NooBaa components once:

oc delete pod noobaa-core-0 -n openshift-storage
oc delete pod noobaa-db-pg-0 -n openshift-storage
oc delete pod -l noobaa-operator=deployment -n openshift-storage

However, based on the logs, I do not expect this to fix it because the admin account is genuinely missing from the database.


